JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South African furniture retailer Steinhoff reported a 45% jump in quarterly sales on Tuesday, boosted by the inclusion of recently acquired businesses.Steinhoff said sales totaled 5.3 billion euros ($5.61 billion) in the quarter ended December thanks in part to a 1.3 billion euro contribution from Mattress Firm and Poundland.The company paid $3.8 billion to buy US-based Mattress Firm last year in a deal that took it across the Atlantic for the first time. It also acquired Britain&#8217;s Poundland in an $800 million deal. ($1 = 0.9439 euros)